# CC PROMPT — v2.34.2 — feat(skills): execution observability + adoption metrics

## What this does

Three pieces of skill infrastructure shipped in prior versions:
- **v2.13.0–13.1** — skill system: spec-first generation, three-layer validation,
  `skill_execute` dispatcher.
- **v2.33.4** — auto-promoter: weekly scan of `agent_actions`, creates
  `skill_candidates` for repeated `(tool, args_shape)` patterns.

We have no visibility into whether any of it is doing useful work. Open
questions with no answer today:
- Is the auto-promoter actually running? When was the last scan?
- Have any candidates been promoted? Approved by whom?
- When a skill runs, does it save time vs. the raw tool chain it replaced?
- Which skills are used, and which are dead code?

This change adds execution tracking, an observable promoter audit trail, and a
Metrics subtab in the Skills view.

Version bump: 2.34.1 → 2.34.2

